  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UNESCO Creative Cities Network (UCCN)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Created in 2004, the UNESCO Creative Cities Network is composed of 180 member cities from 72 countries. Grouped in 7 creative fields (Crafts and Folk Art, Design, Film, Gastronomy, Literature, Media Arts and Music), Creative cities are committed to placing culture and creativity at the heart of their local development plans - in line with the 2030 Agenda for Sustainable Development - and exchanging at the international level.
The UNESCO Secretariat ensures the overall management of the Network. It leads strategic initiatives and flagship projects and coordinates the designation process and Annual Meetings. It supports member cities through capacity building material and workshops, mobilizes fundraising and promotes the Network&apos;s international visibility through communication and advocacy.</narrative>
  </description>
